    "body": "### Problem\n\n`nvim --clean -u repro.lua`\n```lua\nvim.o.scrolloff = math.ceil(vim.o.lines / 2)\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({ 'BufEnter' }, {\n  callback = function()\n    vim.schedule(function() vim.fn.line('w0') end)\n  end,\n})\nvim.cmd.term()\nvim.cmd.startinsert()\nvim.defer_fn(\n  function()\n    vim.api.nvim_chan_send(\n      vim.bo.channel,\n      [[nvim --clean --headless --server $NVIM --remote-expr \"nvim_exec2('tab h so',{})\"]] .. '\\r\\n'\n    )\n  end,\n  100\n)\n```\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCursor on the center of screen (Not top).\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot sure\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuilt from source",
